15/04/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish troops killed 21 Kurdish militants in a clash near the border with Iraq on Thursday (14 April). 
Three Turkish soldiers and a village guardsman were also reported dead in hours of fighting. 
Security officials say several dozen rebels had entered the country early on Thursday. 
Some 600 soldiers and many local village guards backed by helicopters were deployed against them. 
This was the biggest single incident involving Kurdish terrorists in more than five years. 
(AP, Reuters, NTV - 14/04/05)
